main event: A report detailing the observation of 6-7 round disk-shaped objects in Lakewood, California, on March 16, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were moving at a constant speed and altitude of approximately 10,000 ft.,Estimated speed was 3,000 mph,The observers noted a bluish-green light emitted from the objects,The sighting lasted for about 3-5 seconds,The report suggests the possibility of a bolide being observed.
witness description: Ex-Navy pilot, inactive reserve, U.S. Navy, grade of lieutenant
